{"accepted":[{"assertion":"Erdős Problem #996: declared status 'open'. Formalized: yes. Let $n_1<n_2<\\cdots$ be a lacunary sequence of integers, and let $f\\in L^2([0,1])$. Let $f_n$ be the $n$th partial sum of the Fourier series of $f(x)$. Is there an absolute constant $C>0$ such that, if\\[\\| f-f_n\\|_2 \\ll \\frac{1}{(\\log\\log\\log n)^{C}}\\]then\\[\\lim_{N\\to\\infty}\\frac{1}{N}\\sum_{k\\leq N}f(\\{\\alpha n_k\\})=\\int_0^1 f(x)\\mathrm{d}x\\]for almost every $\\alpha$? Current best: Raikov proved the conclusion always holds (for every $f\\in L^2([0,1])$, with no assumption on $\\| f-f_n\\|_2$) if $n_k=a^k$ for some integer $a\\geq 2$. Prize: no. Tags: analysis.","id":"vf_2161e612423b114c","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"Formal-Conjectures statement: Erdos996.erdos_996 https://google-deepmind.github.io/formal-conjectures/theorem/?name=Erdos996.erdos_996.","id":"vf_357e1c2087e80549","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"},{"assertion":"AI-contributions wiki claim — wiki: Full solution.","id":"vf_9fc9f9d32b38d74c","trust":"signed","type":"theoretical"}],"accepted_activity":false,"activity":[],"activity_types":[],"attempt_count":0,"banked_attempt_count":0,"commits":[],"dependency_impact":"none","detail_url":"problems/996.json","draft_proposals":[],"edges":[{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_2161e612423b114c","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:996","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Problem identity derived from the accepted finding's pinned source anchor.","inferred":true,"relation":"describes","source":"vf_357e1c2087e80549","source_root":"sha256:d3db36661e28b7570fc8704bf8455b80d8382beded47d069f2c386144d90a238","target":"erdos:996","trust":"signed"},{"evidence":"Materialized typed link between accepted findings.","inferred":true,"relation":"synthesized_from","source":"vf_3